      <title>Limesurvey randomizing</title>
      <link>/post/2013-06-03-limesurvey-randomizing/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 03 Jun 2013 12:55:47 -0700</pubDate>
      <guid>/post/2013-06-03-limesurvey-randomizing/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;It is kind of an odd problem.&lt;br&gt;
For the following pretty straight forward question: How do I randomise questions within a group in 
&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.limesurvey.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Limesurvey&lt;/a&gt;? It seems to be really hard to find an answer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the help of Jonas I figured out that there is a randomisation option hidden in the ‘Advanced Settings’ section of a question. What you have to do is provide the same number (this is important) for each question in a group that you want to randomise. Limesurvey will then take care of the rest. It did not seem to work if I named the variable with a string, eg, ‘group1’ but only numeric counters work fine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks Jonas! (I would not have finished at all) …&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
